value.PublicRemarks: Charming 3BR, 2BA brick duplex with original hardwood floors and smart updates just steps from The Witch’s Tower in Prospect Park. Stepping in the 1st floor you’ll find a cozy living room; dining room; bedroom; full bathroom; and kitchen with tiled backsplash, stainless steel appliances, and gas oven. Upstairs is a versatile bedroom with large closet. Downstairs is a spacious finished den with heated floors, cedar closet, and updated bathroom. Unit sits on double-lot with fenced-in back yard and expansive front yard with mature trees.  Smart updates throughout the home include central air, Energy Star appliances, updated insulation in the walls & roof, and Pella windows, making the home extremely energy efficient. Live in a signature and iconic residential neighborhood of the city, but with fast access to both downtowns and freeways.  1 driveway stall included with rent; 1 garage stall available for additional $100 per month.

value.PublicRemarks: This lovely home has great curb appeal with brick in the front and metal roofing, while providing a fenced in backyard oasis that's truly unique to the area. The terraced backyard boasts great privacy, an established garden, quiet sitting area amongst mature pines, producing apple trees, 2 clean sheds for extra storage, and plenty of flat space as well. The hardwood floors on the main floor and upstairs are in immaculate condition. Large entry way, mudroom with 2 extra-large closets and laundry room. Open great room with tall vaulted ceilings and fireplace. The kitchen has ample storage with walk in pantry, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances. Deck off the kitchen and separate dining room perfect for entertaining. All bedrooms upstairs with walk in closets. The basement has a family room, spacious sauna with relaxation area and bathroom, as well as multiple storage areas and indoor workshop. Easy access to 2 highways.

value.PublicRemarks: 4BR, 2.5BA home in Linden Hills with custom woodwork and classic charm steps from Bde Maka Ska and Lake Harriet. Walking in from the sunny front porch, you’ll find the cozy entryway leading to the den, living room and dining room with southern exposures and hardwood floors. Updated kitchen features a large peninsula, ample cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, space for a small breakfast table, and leads to the partially covered deck. Upstairs the large master bedroom hosts two closets and honeycomb blinds, two more bedrooms and a full bathroom are also on that level. On the top floor you’ll love the bonus room that can serve as a bedroom, office, playroom or den with its own ¾ bathroom. Basement provides tons of available storage space, 2nd refrigerator, and washer & dryer.
